    {
      "id": "t17",
      "tag": "h3",
      "text": "1. TikTok Creator Rewards Program"
    },
    {
      "id": "t18",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "TikTok pays eligible creators through its Creator Rewards Program based on video performance."
    },
    {
      "id": "t19",
      "tag": "li",
      "text": "Average payout: $0.02 – $0.04 per 1,000 views"
    },
    {
      "id": "t20",
      "tag": "li",
      "text": "Higher payouts for longer, high-quality content"
    },
    {
      "id": "t21",
      "tag": "h3",
      "text": "2. Brand Sponsorships"
    },
    {
      "id": "t22",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "Brand partnerships are the largest income source for many TikTok creators."
    },
    {
      "id": "t23",
      "tag": "li",
      "text": "10K followers: $100 – $500 per sponsored video"
    },
    {
      "id": "t24",
      "tag": "li",
      "text": "100K followers: $500 – $5,000"
    },
    {
      "id": "t25",
      "tag": "li",
      "text": "1M followers: $5,000 – $50,000+"
    },
    {
      "id": "t26",
      "tag": "h3",
      "text": "3. Affiliate Marketing"
    },
    {
      "id": "t27",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "Creators often promote products through affiliate links and earn commissions when followers purchase through those links."
    },
    {
      "id": "t28",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "Affiliate commissions typically range between"
    },
    {
      "id": "t29",
      "tag": "strong",
      "text": "5% and 20%"
    },
    {
      "id": "t30",
      "tag": "h3",
      "text": "4. Selling Products or Merchandise"
    },
    {
      "id": "t31",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "Many TikTok creators sell digital products, merchandise, or services to their audiences."
    },
    {
      "id": "t32",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "This strategy can generate much larger income than platform payouts."
    },
